comment_data.body:
Nothing is wrong
1 -s is already used in the post cache step
2 I wanted to see more verbosity
But I guess it does nothing without -s
I used `-s` before and after the test runs to be able to compare the cache usage.
I see, It's kind of burried in the logs

> I used `-s` before and after the test runs to be able to compare the cache usage.

isn't it the "cache hit rate" from the `-s` output?
So is there any need to do `-s` before running the tests?

The [documentation](https://github.com/hendrikmuhs/ccache-action#usage) does not say that this is necessary. Is it really needed? Does the previous call to `/usr/sbin/update-ccache-symlinks` still work?

comment_data.body:
What's about "Is this needed at all?" It's a setup step for ccache ([invoke ccache via symlink](https://ccache.dev/manual/4.4.1.html#_run_modes)), and if I didn't miss anything, github action only installs the ccache and saves the cache, you should set it up by yourself
I'm pretty sure that this step is necessary
